ðŸ”¹ 1500-Word Informative Summary

Deep Work argues that the ability to focus without distraction on cognitively demanding tasks is becoming increasingly rareâ€”and therefore increasingly valuable. Cal Newport defines deep work as:

Professional activities performed in a state of distraction-free concentration that push your cognitive capabilities to their limit.

In contrast, shallow work includes:

