Minor administrative tasks

Shallow work keeps you busy.
Deep work makes you valuable.

ðŸ§  Why Deep Work Matters

In todayâ€™s world, attention is constantly fragmented. Phones, notifications, and social platforms train the brain to prefer short bursts of stimulation. Over time, this reduces your ability to focus deeply.

Newport argues that those who master deep work will:

Learn complex skills faster

Produce higher-quality output

Become irreplaceable in their field

In a competitive economy, two abilities matter most:

The ability to learn hard things quickly

The ability to produce at an elite level

Both require deep work.

