ðŸ§  The Four Rules of Deep Work
ðŸ”¹ Rule 1: Work Deeply

Deep work does not happen randomly. You must create systems.

Newport suggests 4 philosophies:

Monastic â€“ Eliminate all distractions completely

Bimodal â€“ Divide time between deep focus and open work

Rhythmic â€“ Daily scheduled deep work blocks

Journalistic â€“ Work deeply whenever time appears

The key is scheduling distraction-free time.

ðŸ”¹ Rule 2: Embrace Boredom

Your brain has been trained to crave stimulation.

If you check your phone every few minutes, your brain loses the ability to tolerate focus. Deep work requires mental stamina.

Train your mind by:

Avoiding constant phone use

Resisting immediate distractions

Practicing concentration intentionally

Boredom builds focus strength.

ðŸ”¹ Rule 3: Quit Social Media

Newport does not say eliminate all toolsâ€”but evaluate them critically.

